nodes.bodyText:
This complex ternary statements are overly complicated.  Why not just create an object:
const TITLES = {
    [statisticTypes.ANALYSES]: "Number of Analyses Ran",
    [statisticTypes.PROJECTS]: "Number of Projects Created",
    [statisticTypes.SAMPLES]: "Number of Samples Created",
    [statisticTypes.USERS]: "Number of Users Created",
  };
Then in you JSX:
title={TITLES[chartType]}
I would do the same thing with the large ternary below as well.

